    <section>
      <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>B.Tech:</strong> 10+2 with Physics, Chemistry, and
          Mathematics. Must clear entrance exam (e.g., JEE Main).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>BCA:</strong> 10+2 with any stream (preferably
          Mathematics/Computer Applications).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>BA CS / BSc CS / BSc IT:</strong> 10+2 with
          Mathematics/Science stream (for BSc), Arts or Science stream (for BA
          CS).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Scope & Salary Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>B.Tech CSE:</strong> 4 to 12 LPA (depends on college and
          skills). Scope in software, web dev, AI, cybersecurity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>BCA / BSc CS / BSc IT:</strong> 2.5 to 6 LPA initially. Jobs
          in tech support, dev, testing, database admin.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Career Options After Graduation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>After B.Tech CSE:</strong> Software Engineer, Data Analyst,
          Cybersecurity Expert, System Architect.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>After BCA / BSc CS / BSc IT:</strong> Web Developer, System
          Admin, Support Engineer, App Developer.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Entrance Exams</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>JEE Main & Advanced:</strong> For B.Tech admissions in IITs &
          NITs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>CUET / University Exams:</strong> For BCA, BSc, BA CS
          programs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GATE:</strong> For M.Tech / higher studies / PSU jobs after
          B.Tech.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Example Career Path</h2>
      <p>If you choose B.Tech in CSE and want to study in NIT or IIT:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Appear for <strong>JEE Main</strong> after 12th.</li>
        <li>
          Qualify with a good rank to get admission in <strong>NIT/IIT</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>
          During B.Tech, prepare for <strong>GATE</strong> for M.Tech or get
          placed through campus placements.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

